The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 February is 38,854 (4,497.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 February, there were 1,117 new confirmed cases (129.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 February, there were 1,682 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 34% (565 fewer cases).
